          <div class="date" style="text-align:right;float:right;">7.13.2004</div><br /><br />
     
     
     <font class="TallRed">For everyone here who was born in the 80's! <a name="108977230171674932">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          So to celebrate McGruff's 25th year anniversary the right way, I was told to investigate what happened in 1980. Here is a copy/pasted report of the exact file I handed to the Directors and assistant Directors of Media, Licensing, and PR @ NCPC. They certaining enjoyed my .02$ on Microsoft and comics.<blockquote><strong>The following movies debuted:</strong><br />The Big Red One <br />Coal Miner's Daughter <br />Dressed to Kill <br />The Elephant Man <br />The Empire Strikes Back <br />Gregory's Girl <br />Heaven's Gate <br />The Long Good Friday <br />The Long Riders <br />Melvin and Howard <br />Ordinary People <br />Raging Bull <br />The Return of the Secaucus Seven <br />The Shining <br />Stir Crazy <br />The Stunt Man <br />Tess<br />Used Cars <br /><strong>The following famous people were born:</strong><br />January 1 - Rebekah Teasdale,British model and journalist <br />January 9 - Sergio García, Spanish golfer <br />January 16 - Albert Pujols, baseball player <br />February 11 - Natasha Bobo, actress <br />February 11 - Matthew Lawrence, actor <br />February 12 - Juan Carlos Ferrero, Spanish tennis player <br />February 12 - Christina Ricci, actress <br />February 27 - Chelsea Clinton, daughter of President Bill Clinton <br />March 18 - Alexei Yagudin, figure skater <br />April 21 - Vincent Lecavalier, NHL hockey player <br />June 16 - Joey Yung, Hong Kong singer <br />June 17 - Venus Williams, tennis player <br />June 26 - Jason Schwartzman, actor <br />June 26 - Michael Vick, football quarterback <br />July 6 - Pau Gasol, Catalan NBA star <br />July 7 - Michelle Kwan, figure skater <br />July 10 - Adam Petty, NASCAR driver (d. 2000) <br />July 10 - Jessica Simpson, singer <br />August 26 - Macaulay Culkin, actor <br />September 7 - Mark Prior, baseball pitcher <br />September 12 - Yao Ming, Chinese NBA star <br />September 21 - Kareena Kapoor, Bollywood actress <br />September 30 - Martina Hingis, Swiss tennis player <br />October 13 - Ashanti, US pop music artist <br />October 16 - Sue Bird, WNBA basketball star <br />October 17 - Justin Shenkarow, voice actor ("Harold Berman" from Hey Arnold!)<br />November 17 - Isaac Hanson, musician <br />November 21 - Hank Blalock, baseball player <br />December 19 - Jake Gyllenhaal, actor (The Day After Tomorrow) <br />December 19 - Marla Sokoloff, actress (Full House, The Practice) <br />December 30 - Eliza Dushku, actress <br />Nick Carter - member of The Backstreet Boys, known for their songs Shining Star and The Call.  <br />Christina Aguilera - She is a singer best known for her #1 singles Genie in a Bottle and What a Girl Wants.  She won the Best New Artist Grammy in 2000.<br /><strong>Mentionable New Technology</strong><br />January 5 - Hewlett-Packard announces release of its first personal computer<br />August 25 - Microsoft announces their version of UNIX, Xenix<br />CNN is launched as the first 24 hour a day news network.<br /><br />IBM hires Paul Allen and Bill Gates to create an operating system for a new PC. The pair buy the rights to a simple operating system manufactured by Seattle Computer Products and use it as a template. IBM allows the two to keep the marketing rights to the operating system, called DOS. This marks the beginning of Bill Gates’ reign upon the world with Microsoft’s first job.<br /><br />The first Tandy Color computer is introduced. <br />Iomega is established. (iomega.com)<br />Quantum is founded. (server tape-disk storage company) (quantum.com)<br />The International Association for Human Resource Information Management is founded (IHRIM.com)<br />Steinberger Sound Corporation is founded.  (http://www.nedsteinberger.com/)<br />ARPANET a.k.a. “The Internet” (before it was the internet) overwhelms its limited capacity.<br />October 27 – The first network propagated computer virus completely shuts down the whole internet.<br />Pioneer begins marketing its videodisc (laserdisc) machines.<br />December 12: Apple (Maker of the famous iPod) goes public. Apple's share rises 32% that day, making 40 employees instant millionaires. Jobs, the largest shareholder, makes $217 million dollars alone. Markkula makes $203 million that day, an incomprehensible 220,700% return on investment.<br /><strong><br />Comic books are revolutionized</strong><br />Note:  Frank Miller, author of Daredevil (the blind crime-fighter), changes EVERYTHING by killing a main character that Daredevil had emotional ties to; thus, opening the perspective of character life where they aren’t just Ying versus the Yang but also 3-dimensional people with feelings who have internal struggles to overcome.<br /><br />First appearance of Kitty Pride in X-Men 129 <br />Creation of She Hulk <br />Introduction in super heroes' world of the western hero of the sixties “Ghost Rider” (renamed Night Rider) in Ghost Rider 50  <br />Creation of (comic adaptation) Doctor Who (Marvel Premiere 57)<br /><strong><br />Music</strong><br />Alternative rock and post punk artists like Joy Division (Closer), The Specials (More Specials) and U2 (Boy) achieve some popularity with influential releases; <br /><br />they are accompanied by popular punk and New Wave releases from Devo (Freedom of Choice), Talking Heads (Remain in Light), The Pretenders (Pretenders), The Clash (London Calling) and The Jam (Sound Affects) <br /><br />Hank Sapoznik, The Klezmorim, Kapelye, Andy Statman and the Klezmer Conservatory Band emerge at the forefront of a klezmer revival among Jews in Israel, the US and UK. <br />Artists like Wilfrido Vargas help popularize meringue, drawing on a large Dominican minority internationally in cities like New York .<br /><br />Talking Heads' Remain in Light is the beginning of world beat music.<br /><strong>Sports</strong> (note the shortness of this category; I'm not much into sports.)<br />The 1980 Olympic Games are boycotted by America as a result of the December 1979 invasion of Afghanistan by Soviet troops. (<a href="http://www.80s.com/Entertainment/Sports/Olympics/1980/summer.html">link</a>)</blockquote>Don't forget to read paranoidandroid's post! Hey P.A., you think you can log your travels here on E3R? I *promise* it will remained archived for all time. I still have the post ever made on E3R all the way back from 1999 when it was actually called E3, the electric third. TuuK, I don't want this to look like an excuse for you to start calling it that again. <a href="http://www.e3expo.com/e3expo/">Very infringing.</a><br />
