				I'm on my way to bed, so I just did a quick scan.  "Ying versus the Yang" is actually Yin (submissive, Earth) and Yang (agressive, Heaven).  Just a quick note, that particular misidentification has started to get on my nerves since I began studying Daoism.  The other common mistake related to Daoism that's been bothering me relates to the image commonly referred to as "Yin/Yang".  It is actually called the Gua, which roughly translates to diagram.  I could go on, but I can barely justify what I've already written.  On a less anal note, good work.<br />
